value.value: 丸い眼窩
orbits present a more circular rather than the ususal oval appearance
毛の生えた鼻部
excessive hair growth on or around the muzzle
砧骨の矮小化
reduced size of the anvil-shaped, central bone of the three auditory ossicles which articulates with the head of the malleus anteromedially and the stapes inferomedially
きぬた骨形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the incus, typically resulting in decreased size
砧骨-鐙骨関節の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the small synovial joint located between the lenticular process on the long crus of the incus and the head of the stapes
砧骨-槌骨関節の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the saddle-shaped synovial joint located between the incus and the malleus
きぬた骨-つち骨の融合
bony fusion of the incus and the malleus into a single structure
顎関節の欠如
absence of the synovial articulation between the head of the mandibular condoyloid process and the mandibular fossa and articular tubercle of the temporal bones
頬骨の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the zygomatic bone, typically resulting in decreased size
上顎洞の炎症
local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes in the maxillary sinuses
鼻柱の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the tissue that links the nasal tip to the nasal base, and separates the nares; it is the inferior margin of the nasal septum
鼻尖の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the tip of the nose located at the junction of the inferior margin of the nasal ridge and the columella
鼻尖裂
a splitting of the nasal tip; visually assessable vertical indentation, cleft, or depression of the nasal tip
鼻裂
visually assessable vertical indentation, cleft, or depression of the nasal bridge, ridge and tip
副鼻腔炎
local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes in the mucous membranes of the nose and in one or more paranasal sinuses
鼓室後突起の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the posterior extension of the squamosal bone that lies just above the incus
鼓室後突起の欠如
absence of the posterior extension of the squamosal bone that normally lies just above the incus
側頭鱗骨の 矮小化
reduced size of the anterosuperior portion of the temporal bone that is thin, scale-like, and translucent and forms part of the lateral wall of the cranial vault
鱗状骨形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the temporal bone squamous part, typically resulting in decreased size
耳小骨の矮小化
reduced size of the three bones of the middle ear
耳小骨の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the middle ear ossicle, typically resulting in decreased size
顎骨の矮小化
reduced size of the investing bone that lies on the surface of the malleus
斜頚
involuntary contractions of the neck musculature resulting in an abnormal posture of or abnormal movements of the head
アブミ骨の矮小化
reduced size of the stirrup-shaped ossicle that is the smallest and innermost of the three auditory ossicles
アブミ骨の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the stapes, typically resulting in decreased size
舌の炎症
local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins and leukocytes in the tongue
歯肉の炎症
local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes in the gums
歯周組織の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the specialized tissues that both surround and support the teeth, maintaining them in the maxillary and mandibular bones; it consists of four principal components: the gums (gingiva), periodontal ligament, cementum, and alveolar bone proper
歯周組織の炎症
local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes in the periodontium (including the gums and supporting structures of the teeth)
第三咽頭弓の矮小化

definition.value: reduced size of the third branchial arch

value.value: 第四鰓弓の矮小化
reduced size of the fourth branchial arch
第六咽頭弓の矮小化
reduced size of the sixth branchial arch
下切歯の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the lower set of long teeth that are the most anterior and prominent in the jaw
上顎側切歯の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the upper set of long teeth that are the most anterior and prominent in the jaw
下切歯色異常
anomaly in the color and shading of the lower incisors, which normally presents in shades of white
上切歯色異常
anomaly in the color and shading of the upper incisors, which normally presents in shades of white
顔面筋萎縮

acquired diminution of facial muscle tissue associated with wasting as from death and reabsorption of cells, diminished cellular proliferation, decreased cellular volume, pressure, ischemia, malnutrition, reduced function or malfunction, or hormonal changes; occurs with age, immobilization, weightlessness, malnutrition or denervation
顔面神経麻痺

severe or complete loss of power of voluntary movement in muscles of the face through injury or disease of it or its nerve supply; facial muscles are innervated by the facial nerve (i.e., the seventh cranial nerve)
顔面筋変性
pathological deterioration of facial muscle tissue, often accompanied by loss of function
顔面筋痙攣

sudden, repetitive, nonrhythmic motor movements (spasms) involving the muscles of the face; common types of facial spasms include rapid, repetitive squinting or blinking, grimacing, mouth twitching, and nose twitching
顔面筋の生理異常
any functional anomaly of any of the striated skeletal muscles innervated by the facial nerve (cranial nerve VII) that, among other things, control facial expression
顎二腹筋前腹の形態異常

definition.value: any structural anomaly of the anterior belly of the digastric muscle which arises from a depression on the inner side of the lower border of the mandible called the digastric fossa, close to the symphysis, and passes downward and backward; the anterior body originates from the first pharyngeal arch and is supplied by the trigeminal via the mylohyoid nerve, a branch of the inferior alveolar nerve, itself a branch of the mandibular division of the trigeminal nerve

value.value: 顎二腹筋後腹の形態異常

definition.value: any structural anomaly of the longer, posterior belly of the digastric muscle arising from the mastoid notch which is on the inferior surface of the skull, medial to the mastoid process of the temporal bone; the posterior belly is supplied by the digastric branch of facial nerve

value.value: 顎二腹筋の生理異常

definition.value: any functional anomaly of the digastric muscle whose action elevates the hyoid when the mandible is fixed and depresses the mandible when the hyoid is fixed; when the two bellies of the digastric contract, they pull upward on the hyoid bone; but if the hyoid is fixed from below, the digastric assists in extreme opening of the mouth such as yawning or taking a large bite

value.value: 顎舌骨筋の形態異常

definition.value: any structural anomaly of the flat and triangular paired muscle that runs from the mandible to the hyoid bone forming the muscular floor of the oral cavity of the mouth; it is a suprahyoid muscle derived from the first pharyngeal arch that is situated immediately superior to the anterior belly of the digastric muscle

value.value: 茎突舌骨筋の形態異常

definition.value: any structural anomaly of the slender suprahyoid muscle lying anterior and superior of the posterior belly of the digastric muscle; it arises from the styloid process of the temporal bone and inserts into the body of the hyoid bone; it is perforated, near its insertion, by the intermediate tendon of the digastric muscle; the stylohyoid elevates and retracts the hyoid bone, elongating the floor of the mouth during swallowing

value.value: 茎突舌骨筋の欠如

absence of the slender suprahyoid muscle lying anterior and superior of the posterior belly of the digastric muscle that elevates and retracts the hyoid bone, elongating the floor of the mouth during swallowing
頬筋形態異常

definition.value: any structural anomaly of the thin quadrilateral muscle occupying the interval between the maxilla and the mandible at the side of the face that forms the anterior part of the cheek or the lateral wall of the oral cavity; it compresses the cheeks against the teeth and is used in acts such as blowing; it is an assistant muscle of mastication and in neonates it is used to suckle

label.value: abnormal depressor anguli oris muscle morphology

value.value: 口角下制筋の形態異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal depressor anguli oris muscle morphology

definition.value: any structural anomaly of the facial muscle that originates from the mandible and inserts into the angle of the mouth; it is innervated by the marginal mandibular branch of the facial nerve and receives its blood supply from the facial artery; the muscle depresses the corners of the mouth which is associated with frowning

value.value: 歯髄の炎症

local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes in dental pulp tissue; commonly associated with a bacterial infection but can also be due to other insults such as repetitive trauma or in rare cases periodontitis
